### Documentation Pipeline Commands

Three-phase pipeline for feature documentation â€” from TRD to QA handoff:

| Phase     | Command                                  | When to use    | Inputs                                              |
|-----------|------------------------------------------|----------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Pre-impl  | `/trd {feature or Confluence URL}`       | Before coding  | PRD + Figma + BE TRD + QA TRD + codebase            |
| Post-impl | `/feature-report {feature or URL}`       | After coding   | PRD + codebase (reads actual files)                 |
| QA handoff| `/qa-align {feature or {{JIRA_KEY}}}`    | Before QA      | QA TRD + Compliance Matrix + gap analysis           |

PRD from Confluence is the primary input for `/trd` and `/feature-report`. Jira tickets are optional â€” used for tracking only, not as requirement source.

**Flags:** `--be-trd` (fetch BE TRD from Confluence), `--qa-trd` (fetch QA TRD from Confluence).

**Output locations:**
- `/trd` â†’ `.docs/trd/TRD-{Name}.md`
- `/feature-report` â†’ `.docs/feature-report/{name}/` (README, COMPLIANCE_MATRIX, RESPONSIBILITY_SPLIT, QA_ALIGNMENT, TICKETS)
- `/qa-align` â†’ `.docs/feature-report/{name}/QA_ALIGNMENT.md` or `.docs/qa-alignment/QA-{Name}.md`

