## Coding Guidelines

1. Define the data model before writing code.
2. Start with mock data instead of a database.
3. Create a component library; split code into multiple files.
4. Centralize state management.
5. Batch implementation into smaller chunks.
6. Double-check you're editing the correct files.
7. Ask follow-up questions if requirements are unclear.

## Commit Rules

- Author: from your local git config (`git config user.name` / `user.email`).
- No AI/Claude/Anthropic attribution in commit messages.
- Format: `{type}: {summary} ({{JIRA_KEY}})`
- Types: `feat` (new feature), `fix` (bug fix), `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`.

