## Mistake-Learning Pattern

Three commands (`/do-implementation`, `/breakdown-design`, `/plan-first`) instruct Claude to:

1. **Before starting** â€” read CLAUDE.md Common Issues for known gotchas.
2. **When a mistake happens** â€” add it here with what went wrong + how it was fixed.

This creates a feedback loop: each session learns from past sessions and the knowledge persists in the repo.

## Common Issues / Lessons Learned

Per-system detail lives on dedicated docs in `.docs/common-issues/`. This section keeps cross-cutting gotchas that every `claude -p` session must know.

