### Session discipline â€” 2 gates, every session, no exceptions

1. **Lookup gate Â· every session's first substantive user message.** Pattern-match the incoming question against the subjects in `.docs/common-issues/README.md`. If it hits a known subject/title, answer from the cataloged pattern first â€” don't re-discover what's already indexed.
2. **Save gate Â· before writing any new learning, and again at session end.** Save in this catalog (CLAUDE.md inline or `.docs/common-issues/` chapter), NOT in local memory. Scan catalog first; if a related subject exists, append a dated sub-note rather than create a sibling.

### Size discipline â€” every CLAUDE.md edit ends with `wc -c`

After ANY edit to this file, run `wc -c CLAUDE.md`. If > 40000 chars, trim back below 40000 in the same session before stopping.

### `claude -p` invocation gotchas

- **`set -euo pipefail` + bare `claude -p` = infinite loop.** Any non-zero exit kills the script via `set -e` before the retry handler runs. Suffix with `|| IMPL_EXIT=$?`.
- **`set -u` + undefined variable = silent death.** Typos in variable names kill scripts with no error. Verify variable spelling with `grep -n '<VAR>' script.sh` before relying on it.
- **`--strict-mcp-config` required on every `claude -p` call when using project-local `.mcp.json`.** Otherwise managed integrations (e.g. Claude Team workspace MCPs) outcompete your local ones.

### Shell + cron

- **Do NOT use `CRON_TZ` in crontab.** Ubuntu ISC cron ignores it for scheduling (only sets `$TZ` inside command). Convert times to system TZ at write-in.
- **`set -euo pipefail` + Gradle `--continue`** still exits non-zero. Fix root cause (test errors) rather than suppressing with `set +e`.
- **`grep -c PATTERN file || echo 0` returns `"0\n0"` on empty file.** `grep -c` prints `0` AND exits 1. Fix: `VAR=$(grep -c . "$file" 2>/dev/null) || VAR=0`.

### Confluence API

- **`confluence_update_page` is full-replace.** Always read full page, modify target section only, send complete body back.
- **Markdown round-trip flattens fenced code blocks.** A ` ```bash ` block becomes `Defaultbash# commandâ€¦` in ADF and persists on write-back. Use `contentFormat: "adf"` (Mac MCP) or `contentFormat: "storage"` (VPS MCP) for pages with rich content; markdown only for plain prose.

